Site Identification
Site Name: Gym Experts

Logo: (My friend hasn't provided me with a logo yet)

Description: An intuitive platform designed for people looking to start at the gym or who already have experience. 
I used the name because the routines will be provided by two gym experts, which also makes people more confident in the routines.

Domain Availability (optional): gymexperts.online

2. Site Purpose
The website acts as a management hub for the user. It provides:
- A searchable library of exercises categorized by muscle group.
- An interactive tool to create and save personalized routines.
- A progress tracking system using localStorage so that information persists between sessions.

3. Scenarios (Target Audience)
Beginner User: "What exercises can I do today to work my chest and triceps without needing specialized equipment?" (The site will respond by filtering exercises by muscle group and equipment.)
Recurring user: "How was the weight or the reps I did in my last squat session?" (The site will display the browser's saved history.)

4. Visual Design (Technical Suggestion)
Color Scheme (Contrast Principles)
For a gym website, we suggest a scheme that conveys energy and clarity:

Primary Color (Headings/Buttons): #E63946 (Energetic Red or "Alabastor") - Use it for calls to action ("Save Routine" buttons).
Secondary Color (Backgrounds/Details): #F1FAEE (Off-white) - Ideal for card backgrounds and reading areas.
Accent Color (Text/Footer): #1D3557 (Deep Dark Blue) - Excellent for readability in the body text.

Typography
Titles: Montserrat (Sans-serif, modern and strong).
Body text: Open Sans (Highly legible on mobile devices).

5. Wireframe Guide (Structure)
For your siteplan.html, you will need to draw (or create with simple shapes) these two views:

Mobile View:
Header: Logo + "Hamburger" Menu (vertical navigation).
Hero Section: Motivational title + "Create Routine" button.
Main: Vertically stacked exercise cards.
Footer: Links + References.

Desktop View:

Header: Logo on the left, horizontal menu on the right.
Main: 2 or 3 column layout for the exercise library (CSS Grid).
Sidebar: Optional, for quick routine history.